      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that you feel this way when the effort of pretending becomes exhausting, and it is okay to feel tired of carrying a weight that no longer serves you. The mask you wear is just a temporary shield, but the person behind it is still there, even if they haven't looked healthy in a while. You don't have to figure out who you are right this moment; simply acknowledging how heavy it feels is the first step toward putting it down.",
